<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1270,1726,1805]" box="[382,1089,1784,1805]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology: This species is named after the country where it was found.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,468,635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Remark: This species belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[832,944,468,494]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">paradoxa</emphasis>
-group. The new species is similar to the following two species: 
<emphasis box="[780,958,504,530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authorityName="BERLESE" authorityYear="1884" box="[780,860,504,530]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachyuropodidae" genus="Oplitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Oplitis</taxonomicName>
cubana
</emphasis>
WIŚNIEWSKI &amp; HIRSCH- MANN, 1991 and 
<taxonomicName authority="HIRSCHMANN, 1991" authorityName="HIRSCHMANN" authorityYear="1991" box="[520,924,539,565]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachyuropodidae" genus="Oplitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblita">
<emphasis box="[520,675,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Oplitis oblita</emphasis>
HIRSCHMANN, 1991
</taxonomicName>
. The main differences are the following: the ventral setae of the new species are filiform, but the two known species have blade-like ventral setae.
</paragraph>
